CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 21, 1958, pg. B7 reads: "Ballet Soloist - Miss Andra Dukes is shown performing at the seventh annual AKA Cotillion, held at Syria Mosque recently.  Seventeen young ladies made their debut in the Cotillion. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Ballerina Andra Dukes, performing for "King" and "Queen," in Syria Mosque for the Alpha Kappa Alpha's Seventh Debutante Cotillion
